description:
&lt;p&gt;This action adds a recipient to an envelope on DocuSign. Prior to using this action, Create Draft Envelope from Template action will be used to generate a draft Envelope.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Inputs:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Envelope&lt;/b&gt; - The envelope record that has the envelope ID.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Email&lt;/b&gt; - Email ID of the recipient.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Name&lt;/b&gt; - Name of the recipient.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Role Name&lt;/b&gt; - Role Name from the envelope to which the recipient is to be associated.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Recipient ID&lt;/b&gt; - Recipient ID from the envelope to which the recipient is to be associated.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Embedded Signing Recipient&lt;/b&gt; - Select or drag and drop the  ServiceNow user record to be used for embedded signing. The Email Address ,User Name and User ID fields are extracted from the user record and used for embedded signing. Ensure that the Use Embedded Signing checkbox is checked when using this field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Outputs:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Status&lt;/b&gt; - Will be set to &quot;Success&quot; if the request succeeds or &quot;Error&quot; if a failure occurs.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Error Message&lt;/b&gt; - Will be populated when the status is &quot;Error&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Error Messages:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The specified Integrator Key was not found or is disabled. Please verify the configured credentials.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;User lacks sufficient permission to perform this action.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Provided recipient ID is invalid or does not exist.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The email address for the recipient is invalid or is of incorrect format.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;User Record is not provided or the User Record is missing either the name, email or user ID.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Either Email or Name has not been provided.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To use this action, the corresponding DocuSign connection and credential must be created and associated with the DocuSign Connection &amp; Credential alias.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Additional Note:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Requires a subscription to a DocuSign API Plan that satisfies your feature and transactions requirements. &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.docusign.com/products-and-pricing/api-plans&quot;&gt;Read More&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To use this action, the corresponding DocuSign connection and credential must be created and associated with the DocuSign Connection &amp; Credential alias. &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://docs.servicenow.com/?context=CSHelp:credentials-connections-alias&quot;&gt;Learn More&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note&lt;/b&gt;: Requires a subscription for production use. &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://docs.servicenow.com/?context=CSHelp:IntegrationHub-licensing-information&quot;&gt;Read More&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
